<li>What will 76 do?</li>
<li>What will Mobil do in response?</li>

</ul>

</section>
</section>
<section>
<section id="slide-org8e45542">
<h2 id="org8e45542">Strategic interaction</h2>
<ul>
<li>Game-theoretic situations differ from decision-theoretic (Econ 311) situations because they are <i>strategic</i></li>
<li>When playing a game, a player must consider the other player's preferences when making their choices
<ul>
<li>But the player must <i>also</i> recognize that the other player is considering their preferences as well
<ul>
<li>The first player must also recognize that the other player recognizes that player 1 recognizes that the other player is considering player 1's preferences
<ul>
<li>&#x2026;
<ul>
<li>&#x2026;</li>

</ul></li>

</ul></li>

</ul></li>

</ul></li>

</ul>

</section>
</section>
